description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/transport/ble_ipsp_transport.c
Lines: 556-559

lichen_ble_transport_get_state() reads transport_state.state without holding the mutex:

    enum lichen_ble_conn_state lichen_ble_transport_get_state(void)
    {
        return transport_state.state;
    }

The state field is modified in connected_cb(), disconnected_cb(), and security_changed_cb() while holding the mutex. This is a data race.

Similar issue in lichen_ble_transport_is_secure() at lines 561-564.

Fix: Acquire transport_state.lock before reading state, or document that this is a best-effort snapshot.
